<p>Whenever I'm in the mood for something crispy and spicy, <a href="https://spicecravings.com/indian-snacks">Indian snacks</a> always hit the spot. They offer a satisfying combination of salty, sweet, and tangy flavors, just like this delicious <strong>Aloo Tikki</strong>, also known as <strong>Aloo Tikki Chaat</strong>. </p>



<p><strong>Aloo Tikki</strong> is an Indian spiced potato patty that is <meta charset="utf-8">soft and fluffy in the middle and is fried to golden and crispy deliciousness. This popular snack is an Indian equivalent of American hash browns.  </p>



<p>These tikkis are usually served as-is as a snack with green chutney, with a scoop of spiced yogurt, or as aloo tikki burgers. </p>



<p>This recipe is my easy, homemade take on an authentic street-side Aloo Tikki that comes together in less than 30 minutes. </p>



<h2 id="ingredients-notes-substitutions"   class="wp-block-heading" >Ingredients - Notes &amp; Substitutions</h2>



<p>This aloo tikki recipe is made with a potato and green pea base and an incredible blend of fresh herbs and seasonings. Let's take a look at what we need:</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1800" height="1200" data-pin-nopin="true" data-pin-description="Easy 25-minute recipe for┬ĀAloo Tikki,┬Āa popular north-Indian street food! Mashed┬Āpotato and peas are formed into patties then pan-fried until golden brown and crispy. #indianrecipes #indianvegetarianrecipes #indiansnackrecipe" data-pin-title="Aloo Tikki - Indian-Spiced Potato Patties" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201800%201200'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="ingredients for aloo tikki potato patties in bowls from above" class="wp-image-31375" data-lazy-srcset="https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Ingredients.jpg 1800w, https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Ingredients-300x200.jpg 300w, https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Ingredients-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Ingredients-768x512.jpg 768w, https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Ingredients-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Ingredients-720x480.jpg 720w, https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Ingredients-360x240.jpg 360w, https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Ingredients-180x120.jpg 180w, https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Ingredients-150x100.jpg 150w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1800px) 100vw, 1800px" data-lazy-src="https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Ingredients.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" width="1800" height="1200" data-pin-nopin="true" data-pin-description="Easy 25-minute recipe for┬ĀAloo Tikki,┬Āa popular north-Indian street food! Mashed┬Āpotato and peas are formed into patties then pan-fried until golden brown and crispy. #indianrecipes #indianvegetarianrecipes #indiansnackrecipe" data-pin-title="Aloo Tikki - Indian-Spiced Potato Patties" src="https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Ingredients.jpg" alt="ingredients for aloo tikki potato patties in bowls from above" class="wp-image-31375" srcset="https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Ingredients.jpg 1800w, https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Ingredients-300x200.jpg 300w, https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Ingredients-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Ingredients-768x512.jpg 768w, https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Ingredients-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Ingredients-720x480.jpg 720w, https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Ingredients-360x240.jpg 360w, https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Ingredients-180x120.jpg 180w, https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Ingredients-150x100.jpg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 1800px) 100vw, 1800px" /></noscript><figcaption>Aloo Tikki Ingredients: potatoes, peas, onion, green chili, cilantro, spices, ginger and cornstarch</figcaption></figure></div>



<p><strong>Gold Potatoes:</strong> you will need 3-4 boiled gold potatoes to make the 2 cups of grated potato needed for this recipe. </p>



<p><strong>Green Peas:</strong> frozen or fresh work great. If using frozen, thaw them first.</p>



<p><strong>Onion:</strong> you can use white or red onion depending on your preferences. Be sure to chop it pretty small so that it incorporates well into the patties.</p>



<p><strong>Grated Ginger:</strong> I recommend using <a href="https://spicecravings.com/how-to-cut-ginger">freshly grated ginger</a> for the best flavor.</p>



<p><strong>Serrano Chili:</strong> finely chopped. You can leave the seeds if you love spice, or remove them for more mild heat.</p>



<p><strong>Cilantro:</strong> freshly chopped cilantro adds delicious freshness to these flavorful patties.</p>



<p><strong>Spices: </strong>a blend of Himalayan salt, dry mango powder, chaat masala, coriander powder, cumin powder, and red chili powder/cayenne pepper creates an incredible sweet and spicy flavor. Adjust the amount of red chili powder/cayenne pepper depending on your spice preferences.</p>



<p><strong>Cornstarch: </strong>This helps make firm patties and absorbs moisture to create that crispy exterior. Rice flour or breadcrumbs will work as well.</p>



<p><strong>Oil: </strong>I use avocado or vegetable oil for its neutral flavor, but any clear oil will work for frying.</p>



<p><strong>For Serving: </strong>serve your tikki with <a href="https://spicecravings.com/cilantro-chutney-green-chutney">cilantro chutney</a>, <a href="https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B00BUXM4X2/ref=as_li_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=9325&amp;creativeASIN=B00BUXM4X2&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;tag=arammasalakit-20&amp;linkId=00cb9bd249eb0ec6f6128888a5d5f087" rel="nofollow sponsored noopener" target="_blank">tamarind chutney</a>, or <a href="https://spicecravings.com/instant-pot-yogurt">seasoned yogurt</a>. </p>



<p class="has-background" style="background-color:#f4f4f4">Scroll to the recipe card for a detailed list of ingredients and quantities.</p>



<h2 id="how-to-make-aloo-tikki"   class="wp-block-heading" >How to Make Aloo Tikki</h2>



<p>Here are step-by-step directions on how to make crispy aloo tikki!</p>



<p><strong>Steam the peas:</strong> Add ┬Į cup of water to a frying pan, bring to a simmer, then add in the peas. Cover and cook for 5 minutes. To steam in the microwave, sprinkle water over the peas and microwave for 30 seconds at a time until thawed. </p>



<p><strong>Prepare the potatoes:</strong> Boil the potatoes either on the stove, <a href="https://spicecravings.com/instant-pot-boiled-potatoes">in the instant pot</a>, or in the microwave using the "potatoes" preset. Once they are fork-tender, cool, then grate them to make 2 cups. (pic 1)</p>



<p><strong>Assemble:</strong> In the same mixing bowl, add peas, chopped onion, cilantro, grated ginger, and all of the spices. Mix well, then add in the cornstarch (or rice flour). Mix until fully combined. (pic 2, 3 &amp; 4)</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-full"><img decoding="async" width="2000" height="1600" data-pin-nopin="true" data-pin-description="Easy 25-minute recipe for┬ĀAloo Tikki,┬Āa popular north-Indian street food! Mashed┬Āpotato and peas are formed into patties then pan-fried until golden brown and crispy. #indianrecipes #indianvegetarianrecipes #indiansnackrecipe" data-pin-title="Aloo Tikki" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%202000%201600'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="steps 1-4 of making aloo tikki patties in a mixing bowl" class="wp-image-31381" data-lazy-srcset="https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Steps-1-4.jpg 2000w, https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Steps-1-4-300x240.jpg 300w, https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Steps-1-4-1024x819.jpg 1024w, https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Steps-1-4-768x614.jpg 768w, https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Steps-1-4-1536x1229.jpg 1536w, https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Steps-1-4-720x576.jpg 720w, https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Steps-1-4-360x288.jpg 360w, https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Steps-1-4-180x144.jpg 180w, https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Steps-1-4-150x120.jpg 150w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" data-lazy-src="https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Steps-1-4.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" width="2000" height="1600" data-pin-nopin="true" data-pin-description="Easy 25-minute recipe for┬ĀAloo Tikki,┬Āa popular north-Indian street food! Mashed┬Āpotato and peas are formed into patties then pan-fried until golden brown and crispy. #indianrecipes #indianvegetarianrecipes #indiansnackrecipe" data-pin-title="Aloo Tikki" src="https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Steps-1-4.jpg" alt="steps 1-4 of making aloo tikki patties in a mixing bowl" class="wp-image-31381" srcset="https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Steps-1-4.jpg 2000w, https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Steps-1-4-300x240.jpg 300w, https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Steps-1-4-1024x819.jpg 1024w, https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Steps-1-4-768x614.jpg 768w, https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Steps-1-4-1536x1229.jpg 1536w, https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Steps-1-4-720x576.jpg 720w, https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Steps-1-4-360x288.jpg 360w, https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Steps-1-4-180x144.jpg 180w, https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Steps-1-4-150x120.jpg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></noscript></figure></div>



<p><strong>Form the patties:</strong> Divide the potato mixture into 8 portions. Apply a little bit of oil to your palms and use your hands to shape each portion into a round patty. The patties should be about ┬Į-inch thick. (Pic 5, 6 &amp; 7)</p>



<p><strong>Optional Step: </strong>Rub 1 teaspoon rice flour or cornstarch in your hands and lightly dust each patty with it. Wipe off any excess using a kitchen towel. Dusting is optional, but dries up any excess moisture on the surface and seals the patties, resulting in a crispier tikki. Feel free to skip. (pic 8)</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-full"><img decoding="async" width="2000" height="1600" data-pin-nopin="true" data-pin-description="Easy 25-minute recipe for┬ĀAloo Tikki,┬Āa popular north-Indian street food! Mashed┬Āpotato and peas are formed into patties then pan-fried until golden brown and crispy. #indianrecipes #indianvegetarianrecipes #indiansnackrecipe" data-pin-title="Aloo Tikki - Indian-Spiced Potato Patties" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%202000%201600'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="steps 5-8 of aloo tikki being formed into patties and coated with cornstarch" class="wp-image-31580" data-lazy-srcset="https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Steps-5-6-1.jpg 2000w, https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Steps-5-6-1-300x240.jpg 300w, https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Steps-5-6-1-1024x819.jpg 1024w, https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Steps-5-6-1-768x614.jpg 768w, https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Steps-5-6-1-1536x1229.jpg 1536w, https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Steps-5-6-1-720x576.jpg 720w, https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Steps-5-6-1-360x288.jpg 360w, https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Steps-5-6-1-180x144.jpg 180w, https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Steps-5-6-1-150x120.jpg 150w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" data-lazy-src="https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Steps-5-6-1.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" width="2000" height="1600" data-pin-nopin="true" data-pin-description="Easy 25-minute recipe for┬ĀAloo Tikki,┬Āa popular north-Indian street food! Mashed┬Āpotato and peas are formed into patties then pan-fried until golden brown and crispy. #indianrecipes #indianvegetarianrecipes #indiansnackrecipe" data-pin-title="Aloo Tikki - Indian-Spiced Potato Patties" src="https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Steps-5-6-1.jpg" alt="steps 5-8 of aloo tikki being formed into patties and coated with cornstarch" class="wp-image-31580" srcset="https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Steps-5-6-1.jpg 2000w, https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Steps-5-6-1-300x240.jpg 300w, https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Steps-5-6-1-1024x819.jpg 1024w, https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Steps-5-6-1-768x614.jpg 768w, https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Steps-5-6-1-1536x1229.jpg 1536w, https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Steps-5-6-1-720x576.jpg 720w, https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Steps-5-6-1-360x288.jpg 360w, https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Steps-5-6-1-180x144.jpg 180w, https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Steps-5-6-1-150x120.jpg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></noscript></figure></div>



<p><strong>Fry: </strong>In a frying pan, heat oil on medium-high heat. Once hot, add in the tikkis without overcrowding the pan. Cook until golden brown, for about 4 minutes, then flip and brown on the other side. (pic 9 &amp; 10)</p>



<p class="blockquote"><strong>Frying tip: </strong>Check the temperature of the oil by dropping a small crumb. If it starts sizzling and floats to the top, the oil is ready.</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-full"><img decoding="async" width="2000" height="800" data-pin-nopin="true" data-pin-description="Easy 25-minute recipe for┬ĀAloo Tikki,┬Āa popular north-Indian street food! Mashed┬Āpotato and peas are formed into patties then pan-fried until golden brown and crispy. #indianrecipes #indianvegetarianrecipes #indiansnackrecipe" data-pin-title="Aloo Tikki - Indian-Spiced Potato Patties" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%202000%20800'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="aloo tikki potato patties being fried in a skillet" class="wp-image-31382" data-lazy-srcset="https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Steps-9-10.jpg 2000w, https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Steps-9-10-300x120.jpg 300w, https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Steps-9-10-1024x410.jpg 1024w, https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Steps-9-10-768x307.jpg 768w, https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Steps-9-10-1536x614.jpg 1536w, https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Steps-9-10-720x288.jpg 720w, https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Steps-9-10-360x144.jpg 360w, https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Steps-9-10-180x72.jpg 180w, https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Steps-9-10-150x60.jpg 150w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" data-lazy-src="https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Steps-9-10.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" width="2000" height="800" data-pin-nopin="true" data-pin-description="Easy 25-minute recipe for┬ĀAloo Tikki,┬Āa popular north-Indian street food! Mashed┬Āpotato and peas are formed into patties then pan-fried until golden brown and crispy. #indianrecipes #indianvegetarianrecipes #indiansnackrecipe" data-pin-title="Aloo Tikki - Indian-Spiced Potato Patties" src="https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Steps-9-10.jpg" alt="aloo tikki potato patties being fried in a skillet" class="wp-image-31382" srcset="https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Steps-9-10.jpg 2000w, https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Steps-9-10-300x120.jpg 300w, https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Steps-9-10-1024x410.jpg 1024w, https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Steps-9-10-768x307.jpg 768w, https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Steps-9-10-1536x614.jpg 1536w, https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Steps-9-10-720x288.jpg 720w, https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Steps-9-10-360x144.jpg 360w, https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Steps-9-10-180x72.jpg 180w, https://spicecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Aloo-Tikki-Steps-9-10-150x60.jpg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></noscript></figure></div>



<p><strong>Cool and serve:</strong> Once the tikkis are golden-brown and crispy on both sides, transfer them to a paper towel-lined plate and cool for 5 minutes. Serve with chutney or as desired.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-alternative-method-air-fryer-aloo-tikki">Alternative Method: Air Fryer Aloo Tikki</h3>



<p>Aloo tikki is great cooked in the air fryer as well! Here's how:</p>



<ol class="wp-block-list"><li>Prepare and assemble as instructed.</li><li>Preheat the air fryer to 375┬║F and spray the air fryer basket with cooking spray. </li><li>Place the patties in a single layer in the basket, brush them with oil, then air fry for 4 minutes, flip, brush with oil, and air fry for another 4 minutes or until crispy.</li></ol>



<h2 id="serving-suggestions"   class="wp-block-heading" >Serving Suggestions</h2>



<p>There are a few different ways that you can serve aloo tikki fry.</p>



<p><strong>Snack/appetizer: </strong>Serve your aloo tikki patties with a side of <a href="https://spicecravings.com/cilantro-chutney-green-chutney">cilantro chutney</a> and <a href="https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B00BUXM4X2/ref=as_li_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=9325&amp;creativeASIN=B00BUXM4X2&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;tag=arammasalakit-20&amp;linkId=00cb9bd249eb0ec6f6128888a5d5f087" rel="nofollow sponsored noopener" target="_blank">tamarind chutney</a> for dipping.</p>



<p><strong style="color: initial; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Oxygen-Sans, Ubuntu, Cantarell, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif;">Aloo Tikki Chaat:</strong><span style="color: initial; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Oxygen-Sans, Ubuntu, Cantarell, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif;"> Another popular way to serve aloo tikki is with seasoned <a href="https://spicecravings.com/instant-pot-yogurt">yogurt</a> , <a href="https://spicecravings.com/cilantro-chutney-green-chutney">cilantro</a> and <a href="https://spicecravings.com/tamarind-chutney">tamarind chutney</a>. </span></p>



<p>For aloo tikki chaat, combine ┬Į cup plain yogurt with ┬╝ teaspoon salt, ┬╝ teaspoon roasted cumin powder, ┬╝ teaspoon chaat masala, ┬╝ teaspoon red chili powder, and 2 tablespoons cold water. Drizzle this yogurt over aloo tikki and top with both chutneys. </p>



<p><strong>Entree: </strong>Make your potato patties into an entree and serve them as aloo tikki burgers topped with lettuce, tomato, and sliced onion. Here's a detailed recipe for <a href="https://spicecravings.com/aloo-tikki-burger">Aloo Tikki Burger</a>.</p>



